Romans 8:1.source_text: Οὐδὲν ἄρα νῦν κατάκριμα τοῖς ἐν Χριστῷ Ἰησοῦ.

KJV.text: There is therefore now no condemnation to them which are in Christ Jesus, who walk not after the flesh, but after the Spirit.

ESV.text: There is therefore now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

NIV.text: Therefore, there is now no condemnation for those who are in Christ Jesus.

NLT.text: So now there is no condemnation for those who belong to Christ Jesus.

Luke 17:21.source_text: οὐδὲ ἐροῦσιν· ἰδοὺ ὧδε ἢ ἐκεῖ· ἰδοὺ γὰρ ἡ βασιλεία τοῦ θεοῦ ἐντὸς ὑμῶν ἐστιν.

KJV.text: Neither shall they say, Lo here! or, lo there! for, behold, the kingdom of God is within you.

ESV.text: Nor will they say, ‘Look, here it is!’ or ‘There!’ for behold, the kingdom of God is in the midst of you.

NIV.text: Nor will people say, ‘Here it is,’ or ‘There it is,’ because the kingdom of God is in your midst.

NLT.text: You won’t be able to say, ‘Here it is!’ or ‘It’s over there!’ For the Kingdom of God is already among you.

1 Timothy 2:12.source_text: διδάσκειν δὲ γυναικὶ οὐκ ἐπιτρέπω οὐδὲ αὐθεντεῖν ἀνδρός, ἀλλ’ εἶναι ἐν ἡσυχίᾳ.

KJV.text: But I suffer not a woman to teach, nor to usurp authority over the man, but to be in silence.

ESV.text: I do not permit a woman to teach or to exercise authority over a man; rather, she is to remain quiet.

NIV.text: I do not permit a woman to teach or to assume authority over a man; she must be quiet.

NLT.text: I do not let women teach men or have authority over them. Let them listen quietly.

KJV.text: Thy desire shall be to thy husband, and he shall rule over thee.

ESV.text: Your desire shall be contrary to your husband, but he shall rule over you.

NIV.text: Your desire will be for your husband, and he will rule over you.

NLT.text: And you will desire to control your husband, but he will rule over you.

KJV.text: Cast thy bread upon the waters: for thou shalt find it after many days.

ESV.text: Cast your bread upon the waters, for you will find it after many days.

NIV.text: Ship your grain across the sea; after many days you may receive a return.

NLT.text: Send your grain across the seas, and in time, profits will flow back to you.
